        "date":  "2026-06-25",
        "theme":  "Strategy",
        "summary":  "CIOs face mounting pressure to accelerate AI adoption while managing associated governance and compliance risks. The article explores how IT leaders are structuring AI oversight through risk frameworks and maturity models, featuring insights from executives at Hi Marley and Zuora. Leaders are experimenting with organizational structures that separate AI experimentation from production governance.",
        "execSummary":  "Enterprise AI leaders are caught between two equally dangerous failure modes: moving too slowly and losing competitive ground, or moving too fast and creating unmanageable risk exposure. The organizations finding success are installing dual-track governance ΓÇö a fast lane for experimentation with defined guardrails, and a formal lane for production deployment. For customer-support and operations leaders, this means building AI governance as a capability, not just a policy. The caveat: maturity models only work if executive leadership actively enforces the separation between experimental and production AI.",
